                     <summary>Bruloff. On the S face is a classical mourning scene consisting of several figures, seated and standing, some adult and some children. There is also a dog. On the N face is a classical figure (possibly Apollo) with a lyre and a staff, and a pair of wings. He is seated. There is also a severed head and what looks like an artists palette and paint brush. On each of the corners towards the top are what appear to be candlestick holders.</summary>
